snippet.title: DJ Ginge Coldwell Balcony News Broadcast 27th November 2021
snippet.description:
Saturday  - Live Broadcast, from DJ Ginge  Coldwell in Macardo, Zakynthos, Greece 
Today's Topic,
* National Covid Stats for Greece
*  Case's on Zakynthos on National Stats shown in 24 hour's
*A weather front moving across western Greece claimed the life of a 65-year-old man on Friday in Ilia after his car was swept away by a flash flood.
*Extensive damage was caused by the unprecedented bad weather that "swept" Zakynthos in the early morning hours of Friday.
*The Association of Accountants of Tax Professionals of Zakynthos Prefecture informed about an incident of fraudulent taxpayer reclaiming scam in Zakynthos. 
*The Greek government said on Friday it will decide on whether to issue a travel ban similar to the ones announced by the United Kingdom and Israel ,
*As Belgium confirms it’s first case of the South African Covid variant designated ‘Omicron’, the European Commission has advised all member states to impose an emergency ban on all flights into the EU from South Africa,
*A study in Belgium by the Sciensano Institute of Public Health, has concluded that in the age group 55 – 64, those unvaccinated are 47 times more likely to die from a Covid infection, than those who are fully vaccinated.
*UK the Office of National Statistics was Slapped Down by UK Statistics Watchdog For Misleading Claim that Unvaccinated Have “32 Times” Risk of Covid Death,
*An Athens prosecutor is examining two case files from the police cybercrime unit that implicate up to 20 people in violations of the law regarding the spread of fake news about the coronavirus pandemic.
*Greek Police received more reports of domestic violence in the first nine months of this year than in in the whole of 2019 and 2020, a conference on Thursday heard,
